<h2>a poem about a stray dog </h2> <br />
<p>there once was a stray dog</p>
<p>always loyal to his many owners</p>
<p>but they were never loyal to him</p>
<br />
<p>he was young and happy</p>
<p>when he first got adopted</p>
<p>bouncing with joy</p>
<p>still when they left him</p>
<br />
<p>older now, but still friendly</p>
<p>some people came and gave him a new home</p>
<p>but eventually like the last</p>
<p>they left him in the past</p>
<br />
<p>now hes an old dog</p>
<p>not trusting society</p>
<p>not a broken bone in his body</p>
<p>but a broken heart</p>
<br />
<p>humans now are angry</p>
<p>"what a distrustworthy animal", they say</p>
<p>"no wonder they left him here", they say</p>
<p>when he threatens to bite them,</p>
<p>the try to kill him</p>
<p>not knowing that their own actions</p>
<p>made a happy pup</p>
<p>a stray dog</p>
<br />
